CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 19, 1945, pg. 4 reads: "Popular Matron Buried - Widely known throughout the city, the popular Mattie Mills Jones (inset), who died suddenly here was buried from the Church of God, Paulson Avenue, recently. Mrs. Jones was the wife of Emmett Jones who was induated into the Armed Services just two days before she passed away.  Cain funeral establishment was in charge. - Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Six men carrying casket of Mattie Mills Jones, out of Church of God, at 309 Paulson Avenue
